reviewText:
A nice puzzle-platform (no shooting, no time to beat) where puzzles are based on your ability to create and control clones of yourself. Storyline is OK, graphics are nice and controls are very good. Mechanics of cloning may resemble Cloning Clyde but works in a different way:

- Clones are not created beside you, instead you aim your one-of-a-kind gun and shoot" to create them on the place you want (must have line of sight);

- Number of clones is always limited to 4 (you need to delete clones to be able to create other clones on other places);

- All clones mimick your moves

Deep... into consciouness.
Great system mechanics, not fully explored..
7.5/10 difficulty;
1man mastered;
Metroid styled;
VVVVV exploration;
Doom3 ambience;
Twinsen's melancholy;
Braid puzzle-flow;
Limbo loneliness;
Totally mersmerizing... not to mention the honest commitment with the story integrity and it's profound significance.
Wonderful. And powerfully *wondering...
